Author-Name: JIN-MO KIM 
Title: The Geography of Block Acquisitions 
Abstract:
 Using a large sample of partial block acquisitions, we examine the
 importance of geographic proximity in corporate governance and target
 returns. We find that block acquirers have a strong preference for
 geographically proximate targets and acquirers that purchase shares in
 such targets are more likely to engage in post-acquisition target
 governance activities than are remote block acquirers. Moreover, the
 targets of these acquirers realize higher announcement returns and better
 post-acquisition operating performance than do targets of other types of
 acquirers, particularly when they face greater information asymmetries. Copyright (c) 2008 The American Finance Association. 
