Author-Name: JOHN Y. CAMPBELL 
Author-Name: JENS HILSCHER 
Author-Name: JAN SZILAGYI 
Title: In Search of Distress Risk 
Abstract:
 This paper explores the determinants of corporate failure and the pricing
 of financially distressed stocks whose failure probability, estimated from
 a dynamic logit model using accounting and market variables, is high.
 Since 1981, financially distressed stocks have delivered anomalously low
 returns. They have lower returns but much higher standard deviations,
 market betas, and loadings on value and small-cap risk factors than stocks
 with low failure risk. These patterns are more pronounced for stocks with
 possible informational or arbitrage-related frictions. They are
 inconsistent with the conjecture that the value and size effects are
 compensation for the risk of financial distress. Copyright (c) 2008 The American Finance Association. 
