Author-Name: JOSHUA M. POLLET 
Author-Name: MUNGO WILSON 
Title: How Does Size Affect Mutual Fund Behavior? 
Abstract:
 If actively managed mutual funds suffer from diminishing returns to scale,
 funds should alter investment behavior as assets under management
 increase. Although asset growth has little effect on the behavior of the
 typical fund, we find that large funds and small-cap funds diversify their
 portfolios in response to growth. Greater diversification, especially for
 small-cap funds, is associated with better performance. Fund family growth
 is related to the introduction of new funds that hold different stocks
 from their existing siblings. Funds with many siblings diversify less
 rapidly as they grow, suggesting that the fund family may influence a
 fund's portfolio strategy. Copyright (c) 2008 The American Finance Association. 
